This job is no joke.

878
01:03:32,266 --> 01:03:33,643
How did that lady--

879
01:03:33,726 --> 01:03:35,436
It's "Ms. Jang," not "lady."

880
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:38,397
Hey, how could a writer
misuse appellations?

881
01:03:39,190 --> 01:03:41,609
Why are you so irritated today?

882
01:03:44,320 --> 01:03:46,405
By the way, where did she go?

883
01:03:46,489 --> 01:03:48,115
She's at a construction site.

884
01:03:48,199 --> 01:03:49,242
A construction site?

885
01:03:50,201 --> 01:03:51,160
She works there?

886
01:04:09,804 --> 01:04:14,016
If you keep being mad at me,
I might not let you out of the car.

887
01:04:14,100 --> 01:04:16,853
I might leave everything
up to Mi-jo and Joo-hee

888
01:04:16,936 --> 01:04:20,147
and just go for a drive instead.

889
01:04:21,190 --> 01:04:22,358
Whatever.

890
01:04:30,074 --> 01:04:33,953
Sir, could we enlarge
the kitchen by a meter?

891
01:04:35,204 --> 01:04:36,581
-Yes, it's possible.
-Really?

892
01:04:36,664 --> 01:04:38,082
It'll become quite spacious.

893
01:04:39,041 --> 01:04:40,334
That's good.

894
01:04:40,418 --> 01:04:43,671
Also, could you turn that storage room

895
01:04:43,754 --> 01:04:46,215
into a resting area for two people?

896
01:04:46,299 --> 01:04:47,800
Sure. That won't be a problem.

897
01:04:47,884 --> 01:04:52,513
I see. Could you also install a heater
underneath to make it as warm as possible?

898
01:04:57,768 --> 01:05:02,106
Guys, I think they bought this
when I just got into elementary school.

899
01:05:02,189 --> 01:05:04,150
You're right. It's an artifact.

900
01:05:04,233 --> 01:05:06,903
We should donate it to a museum…

901
01:05:11,991 --> 01:05:14,869
Hey, these are too old.

902
01:05:14,952 --> 01:05:16,746
Let's get rid of them.

903
01:05:16,829 --> 01:05:18,915
My mom would never. We need to do it.

904
01:05:18,998 --> 01:05:21,459
My mom can't get rid of things either.
No mom can.

905
01:05:21,542 --> 01:05:23,002
-I'll put them outside.
-Okay.

906
01:05:23,085 --> 01:05:26,464
Right. Microplastics are harmful. Right?

907
01:05:28,799 --> 01:05:30,801
-Oh, my gosh!
-What is it?

908
01:05:30,885 --> 01:05:33,095
What's wrong? Check on her.

909
01:05:33,179 --> 01:05:35,348
-What's wrong?
-What is it?

910
01:05:35,932 --> 01:05:37,266
-Hyeon-jun.
-What?

911
01:05:40,311 --> 01:05:42,813
I'm not seeing things, am I?

912
01:05:42,897 --> 01:05:46,150
No, you're not. It's me, Park Hyeon-jun.

913
01:05:46,233 --> 01:05:47,401
How did you get here?

914
01:05:47,485 --> 01:05:48,444
I drove.

915
01:05:49,695 --> 01:05:52,365
I came because I was too hurt
to make jjajangmyeon.

916
01:05:53,616 --> 01:05:56,452
I'm glad you're here.
I'm so happy that I could cry.

917
01:05:56,535 --> 01:05:59,246
How did you know this place?
Did I give you the address?

918
01:05:59,330 --> 01:06:02,041
This is the only
Jeong's Kitchen in Yangpyeong.

919
01:06:02,124 --> 01:06:04,710
But why are you so upset?

920
01:06:05,461 --> 01:06:07,338
Is there no loyalty among us?

921
01:06:13,094 --> 01:06:14,095
You're right.

922
01:06:14,929 --> 01:06:17,807
Every time something came up,
I let you meet at my restaurant.

923
01:06:18,307 --> 01:06:20,643
Shouldn't you consider me a crew member?

924
01:06:20,726 --> 01:06:22,687
But why didn't you call me over?

925
01:06:23,354 --> 01:06:25,064
I agree. Why didn't you?

926
01:06:25,147 --> 01:06:26,941
You should have, Joo-hee.

927
01:06:27,441 --> 01:06:31,988
Well, I didn't because I felt bad
that you'd have to close the restaurant.

928
01:06:32,071 --> 01:06:35,866
Come on,
closing for just a day won't hurt.

929
01:06:35,950 --> 01:06:38,160
Why leave a chef
out of a kitchen renovation?

930
01:06:38,244 --> 01:06:40,204
This is your bad.

931
01:06:40,287 --> 01:06:43,916
Joo-hee, don't do this.
You're really hurting my feelings.

932
01:06:48,295 --> 01:06:49,380
Chan-young.

933
01:06:50,214 --> 01:06:51,507
I made some porridge.

934
01:06:51,590 --> 01:06:53,175
Aren't I good? Aren't I sweet?

935
01:06:53,259 --> 01:06:54,385
Her mother made some--

936
01:06:54,468 --> 01:06:56,095
Give that to me.

937
01:06:56,178 --> 01:06:58,848
If it wasn't for you,
I would've starved all day.

938
01:06:58,931 --> 01:07:01,100
Hey, let's order in something too.
I'm famished.

939
01:07:01,183 --> 01:07:03,144
-What should we have?
-I want jjajangmyeon.

940
01:07:03,227 --> 01:07:04,979
-What?
-I want jjamppong.

941
01:07:05,730 --> 01:07:09,358
Come on.
You know I make those all the time.

942
01:07:09,442 --> 01:07:10,901
Their tangsuyuk is amazing.

943
01:07:11,694 --> 01:07:13,029
-Get a set.
-What do you want?

944
01:07:13,112 --> 01:07:14,155
-Two sets.
-I want…

945
01:07:18,993 --> 01:07:21,746
JEONG'S KITCHEN

946
01:07:41,974 --> 01:07:43,017
Let me do it.

947
01:07:43,100 --> 01:07:44,852
-Thank you.
-Just sit down.

948
01:07:45,644 --> 01:07:46,771
Aren't you glad I came?

949
01:07:48,647 --> 01:07:50,399
What? Are you not happy?

950
01:07:50,983 --> 01:07:52,943
Should I just go home?

951
01:07:53,027 --> 01:07:55,404
Just help out since you're here anyway.

952
01:07:58,866 --> 01:08:00,117
It's snowing.

953
01:08:01,827 --> 01:08:03,704
It's snowing!

954
01:08:04,830 --> 01:08:05,915
It's so pretty.

955
01:08:09,627 --> 01:08:12,171
It's so pretty.

956
01:08:13,923 --> 01:08:15,591
-Is this the first snow?
-So pretty.

957
01:08:15,674 --> 01:08:16,717
-It's so white.
-Right.

958
01:08:18,052 --> 01:08:19,053
It's nice.

959
01:08:19,929 --> 01:08:22,098
-It was good, right? I told you so.
-Yes.

960
01:08:23,766 --> 01:08:25,851
Does that karaoke machine even work?

961
01:08:27,061 --> 01:08:27,895
Probably.

962
01:08:28,896 --> 01:08:30,898
Joo-hee, sing a song for us.
A seductive one.

963
01:08:30,981 --> 01:08:33,025
Come on. What's wrong with you?

964
01:08:33,109 --> 01:08:36,445
Hey, why would you make
the worst singer sing and ruin the vibe?

965
01:08:37,154 --> 01:08:38,364
Go on. I'm curious.

966
01:08:38,447 --> 01:08:40,699
No. I'm not going to sing.

967
01:08:40,783 --> 01:08:42,451
No, thanks. I won't do it.

968
01:08:45,830 --> 01:08:47,665
Three, three.

969
01:08:50,334 --> 01:08:51,669
It works.

970
01:08:51,752 --> 01:08:52,878
Applause!

971
01:08:57,091 --> 01:08:58,342
It's been ages.

972
01:09:11,772 --> 01:09:16,152
You're getting the feeling
You're getting butterflies

973
01:09:16,235 --> 01:09:21,699
Until when will you steal glances at me?

974
01:09:21,782 --> 01:09:27,621
Tell me how you feel
Don't play dumb

975
01:09:27,705 --> 01:09:31,417
Just follow your heart

976
01:09:31,500 --> 01:09:34,587
And hold my hand

977
01:09:48,225 --> 01:09:49,810
-Okay. Mi-jo, next.
-Next.

978
01:09:49,894 --> 01:09:51,270
-You go.
-What?

979
01:09:51,353 --> 01:09:52,688
You can sing the full song.

980
01:09:52,771 --> 01:09:54,773
You should sing. You have a favorite song.

981
01:09:54,857 --> 01:09:56,775
"About Romance", right?

982
01:09:56,859 --> 01:09:59,069
You might as well just live together now.

983
01:09:59,153 --> 01:10:01,280
You know practically everything about her.

984
01:10:01,363 --> 01:10:02,448
No, thanks.

985
01:10:02,531 --> 01:10:04,950
My voice cracks when I sing it sober.

986
01:10:05,034 --> 01:10:07,161
It's okay. I sang just fine.

987
01:10:08,078 --> 01:10:09,121
Unbelievable.

988
01:10:12,082 --> 01:10:13,334
Go on.

989
01:10:13,417 --> 01:10:15,169
-Hurry. Sing for us.
-Come on.

990
01:10:15,252 --> 01:10:16,337
-Jeez.
-Hurry up.

